  "id": 132780,
  "referenceId": 108834,
  "name": "Acts 6:1–7",
  "localizedName": "Acts 6:1–7",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus' 12 apostles continued to pray and to teach God’s word. More and more people joined the community of people who trusted and obeyed Jesus."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "But they faced problems as they tried to live together in "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108211",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "peace"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Widows from one people group were being treated unfairly. That went against how Jesus taught his followers to live. He had taught them to treat others with love and to give freely."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The apostles needed to keep praying and doing the work of teaching God’s word. So the believers appointed other servants in their community. They served as "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108100",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "deacons"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and made sure that everyone was treated fairly. They made sure that everyone received the food they needed."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The problem was taken care of through prayer and "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108325",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "wisdom"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " from the Holy Spirit. It was also taken care of through the community working together."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In Jerusalem, many saw how the believers lived. They heard God’s word preached. More and more people started to follow Jesus. This included many "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108333",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "priests"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
